what_worked: Applied prefetch_fact_join, multi_dimension_prefetch, single_pass_aggregation: Applied aggressive prefetch restructuring by: (1) creating filtered_dates CTE to pre-filter date range once, (2) creating filtered_sales CTE to compute store-item revenue in single pass, (3) computing store averages from filtered_sales in separate CTE, (4) joining these CTEs for the low-revenue filter before final dimension joins.
why_it_worked: Pre-joining filtered dimensions with fact table before aggregation reduces join input; Pre-filtering multiple dimension tables in parallel reduces join fan-out; Consolidating repeated scans into CASE aggregates reduces I/O from N scans to 1
